    "body": "### Problem\n\nActually, I'm not entirely sure how to describe this issue, nor whether it's a bug. Please verify based on the reproduction steps.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. test.lua\n```lua\nlocal cmd_prompt = \"\"\n\nfunction _G.stl()\n        return \"#mode => \" .. vim.api.nvim_get_mode().mode .. \" #prompt => \" .. cmd_prompt\nend\n\nvim.o.stl = \"%!v:lua.stl()\"\n\nvim.ui_attach(vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"test\"), {\n        ext_cmdline = true,\n        ext_messages = true,\n}, function(event, ...)\n        if event == \"cmdline_show\" then\n                _, _, _, cmd_prompt = ...\n        elseif event == \"mode_change\" then\n        else\n                return\n        end\n        vim.cmd.redraws()\nend)\n```\n\n2. `nvim --clean --cmd \":luafile test.lua\"`\n3. Type `aa` -> `<ESC>` -> `:q` -> `<CR>`\n5. See the statusline\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo prompt\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n/\n\n### Installation\n\nrelease",
